  58:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     ==================================
  59:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c **** 
  60:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     [..]
  61:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     The compilation define USE_HAL_USART_REGISTER_CALLBACKS when set to 1
  62:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     allows the user to configure dynamically the driver callbacks.
  63:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c **** 
  64:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     [..]
  65:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     Use Function @ref HAL_USART_RegisterCallback() to register a user callback.
  66:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     Function @ref HAL_USART_RegisterCallback() allows to register following callbacks:
  67:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) TxHalfCpltCallback        : Tx Half Complete Callback.
  68:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) TxCpltCallback            : Tx Complete Callback.
  69:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) RxHalfCpltCallback        : Rx Half Complete Callback.
  70:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) RxCpltCallback            : Rx Complete Callback.
  71:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) TxRxCpltCallback          : Tx Rx Complete Callback.
  72:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) ErrorCallback             : Error Callback.
  73:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) AbortCpltCallback         : Abort Complete Callback.
  74:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) RxFifoFullCallback        : Rx Fifo Full Callback.
  75:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) TxFifoEmptyCallback       : Tx Fifo Empty Callback.
  76:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) MspInitCallback           : USART MspInit.
  77:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) MspDeInitCallback         : USART MspDeInit.
  78:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     This function takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle, the Callback ID
  79:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     and a pointer to the user callback function.
  80:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c **** 
  81:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     [..]
  82:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     Use function @ref HAL_USART_UnRegisterCallback() to reset a callback to the default
  83:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     weak (surcharged) function.
  84:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     @ref HAL_USART_UnRegisterCallback() takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle,
  85:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     and the Callback ID.
  86:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     This function allows to reset following callbacks:
  87:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) TxHalfCpltCallback        : Tx Half Complete Callback.
  88:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     (+) TxCpltCallback            : Tx Complete Callback.
