  98:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c **** 
  99:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     [..]
 100:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     By default, after the @ref HAL_USART_Init() and when the state is HAL_USART_STATE_RESET
 101:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     all callbacks are set to the corresponding weak (surcharged) functions:
 102:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     examples @ref HAL_USART_TxCpltCallback(), @ref HAL_USART_RxHalfCpltCallback().
 103:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit functions that are respectively
 104:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     reset to the legacy weak (surcharged) functions in the @ref HAL_USART_Init()
 105:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     and @ref HAL_USART_DeInit() only when these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
 106:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     If not, MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the @ref HAL_USART_Init() and @ref HAL_USART_DeInit(
 107:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand).
 108:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c **** 
 109:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     [..]
 110:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in HAL_USART_STATE_READY state only.
 111:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     Exception done MspInit/MspDeInit that can be registered/unregistered
 112:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     in HAL_USART_STATE_READY or HAL_USART_STATE_RESET state, thus registered (user)
 113:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used during the Init/DeInit.
 114:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     In that case first register the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 115:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     using @ref HAL_USART_RegisterCallback() before calling @ref HAL_USART_DeInit()
 116:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     or @ref HAL_USART_Init() function.
 117:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c **** 
 118:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     [..]
 119:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     When The compilation define USE_HAL_USART_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 120:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     not defined, the callback registration feature is not available
 121:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_usart.c ****     and weak (surcharged) callbacks are used.
